    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-26T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="150"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23713: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-26T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. Your April 24, noon.</p>
                <p>Consul Dawson telegraphed April 22<note n="9" xml:id="d150fn9">Telegram not
                        printed.</note> that rebel attack upon Tuxpam April 21 was unsuccessful, but
                    that consular agent has requested protection as situation considered critical.
                    Dawson added that senior American naval officer at Tampico has ordered destroyer
                        <hi rend="italic">Thornton</hi> to proceed to Tuxpam.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
